**CWE-22 Path Traversal**
=======================

CWE-22, also known as "Path Traversal," is a type of vulnerability that occurs when an application allows an attacker to access files or directories outside the intended scope by manipulating the path to a file.

**Example Vulnerability**
------------------------

Consider a simple Node.js web server that serves files from a user-uploaded directory:
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const fs = require('fs');

const app = express();

app.get('/file/:filename', (req, res) => {
  const filename = req.params.filename;
  const filePath = `./uploads/${filename}`;
  fs.readFile(filePath, (err, data) => {
    if (err) {
      res.status(404).send('File not found');
    } else {
      res.send(data);
    }
  });
});
```
In this example, an attacker can manipulate the `:filename` parameter to access files outside the `/uploads` directory by using a path traversal attack. For instance:

*   `http://example.com/file/../../../etc/passwd`: This would attempt to read the contents of the `/etc/passwd` file on the server.
*   `http://example.com/file/%2e%2e/%2e%2e/etc/passwd`: This is a URL-encoded version of the previous example.

